Make MatrixBase a plain class instead of an EnableRCPFromThis<MatrixBase> subclass.

This reverts a SymForce-fork-only change ("[SymEngine] Skydio patch", 2021); upstream
SymEngine never had this inheritance and uses a plain `class MatrixBase`.

EnableRCPFromThis<T> carries the intrusive reference counter used by RCP-managed
objects. With WITH_SYMENGINE_THREAD_SAFE (forced on by openmp, or set directly) that
counter is a std::atomic<unsigned int>, which is non-copyable. That deletes the
implicit copy ops of MatrixBase and hence DenseMatrix's `= default` copy
assignment/ctor, while diophantine.cpp et al. use DenseMatrix as a value type
(copy-assignment, std::vector<DenseMatrix>) -> hard "use of deleted function" build
errors. In the default (plain unsigned int) build the counter is trivially copyable,
so the contradiction is silently masked.

The inheritance is vestigial here: no matrix is ever held in an RCP or uses
rcp_from_this() anywhere in symengine/symenginepy/symforce, so dropping it is
behavior-preserving and lets the thread-safe / OpenMP build compile.

--- a/symengine/matrix.h
+++ b/symengine/matrix.h
@@ -7,9 +7,8 @@ namespace SymEngine
 namespace SymEngine
 {
 
-// TODO(hayk): It's pretty lame that this doesn't inherit from the Basic type
-// and skirts around all the visitor patterns
-class MatrixBase : public EnableRCPFromThis<MatrixBase>
+// Base class for matrices
+class MatrixBase
 {
 public:
     virtual ~MatrixBase(){};
